<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12475&amp;p=143124#p143124"><![CDATA[
One could pedantically argue that the PIC24 / dsPIC microcontrollers are 24-bit (24-bit wide instructions, 16-bit wide data path). <br /><br />That said, we have had &quot;real&quot; (i.e. not just address bus width) non-power-of-two computers before, with 12, 18, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/36-bit" class="postlink">36</a>, 48, and 60-bit data paths.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Sun Mar 15, 2015 6:50 pm</p><hr />
